OL,3,CMother and son with rare heart
OL,4,Ccondition say transplants saved both
OL,5,Ctheir lives
OL,7,F"That's because sometimes families
OL,8,Fdon't feel like they can support organ
OL,9,Fdonation at the point they're asked to
OL,10,Fsupport it.
OL,12,F"If you know that you want to be an
OL,13,Forgan donor, in the event of your
OL,14,Fdeath, the most important thing is to
OL,15,Ftell your loved ones that that's what
OL,16,Fyou want to happen."
